name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @WLOX @scottdelano There’s not a better example of a conservative policy than education savings accounts. Getting gov’t out of the way and giving parents (individuals) more control over their children’s education. Those tax dollars came from those parents’ back pockets, no?

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @WLOX @scottdelano But aren’t those EDU dollars meant to educate ALL students in MS? Traditional public schools work for the vast majority of our students, but not ALL. Shame on us if we don’t find & fund the options that do work for them, and then free their parents up to make that decision.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @WLOX @scottdelano If you’re suggesting I’m against accountability and transparency when it comes to tax dollars being spent in education, you couldn’t be further from the truth.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @WLOX @scottdelano I’m supportive of all educational options. I attended traditional public schools (TPS) and have a child in a TPS. Are you really suggesting I don’t want my child to have the best education possible at her TPS?

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @WLOX @scottdelano Nothing sneaky about believing parents should be able to choose what educational option works best for their children. I’m extremely supportive of parents having more control over the education of their children. 1/2

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @LRNmom @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx Do Santa’s elves make that? Shoot me an email to mwatson@senate.ms.gov, I’ll cover the paper!

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx Wait, we could have been friends until you said “Roll Tide”. Ha! Have a good one! #HoddyToddy

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @LRNmom @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx What’s adequate to you may be inadequate or more than adequate to others. Very subjective term.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx So you understand they have more to spend. With that established, tell me where you’d make cuts to our current spending to offset the increase to Edu. Veterans affairs? Medicaid? Corrections? Transportation? National Guard? Dept. Of Agriculture? MDEQ?

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx Thanks for clarifying that you’re only talking about one subject. I appreciate your engagement and work in the classroom. I had many phenomenal teachers coming up through public schools in MS. Enjoy your Saturday!

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx Gotcha. Are you working off the assumption that we have as much money to spend, in total, as those other states?

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @LRNmom @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx Please define adequate.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx Must have misunderstood your use of “rebaked” and the suggestion that MS teachers wrote them. As for the reason to rename, you’re dead on. It’s a classic example of gov’t/bureaucrats lying to their employers - hardworking MSpians. Thanks for your honesty there...

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx I hope you’re not arguing that CCSS were thrown in the garbage and MS completely rewrote our own standards. That’d be a lie. Re: underfunding public ed, serious question here: how much is enough? Edu spending is a priority in MS & it currently receives more $$ than ever before.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx I'm very familiar w/ how we rebaked the common core casserole & renamed it. Many other states did the same & told their voters they got rid of Common Core too...but they lied. I've spent many hours studying CCSS & have talked to numerous teachers. Perhaps you should too.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @LRNmom That's right. Congrats...this year!

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: Two of my three daughters sing this almost every day. This literally made me laugh out loud. Well done, State! #BabyLandSharks  https://t.co/5s5R9s6joy

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @LRNmom @cindyhydesmith And, Happy Thanksgiving!

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx By the way, Happy Thanksgiving!

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @carriebartlett @cindyhydesmith @MayorHalMarx I have, 100s of times. Are you saying your local district selected Common Core? Someone lied to you if that's the case. The state board adopted CCSS sight unseen on the hopes of receiving Fed $$ in return. As a whole, CCSS is garbage, but it does have a few good pieces.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: @LRNmom @cindyhydesmith I'm sure @cindyhydesmith wants the best Edu possible for all children, but we both believe those decisions are better made on the local level. Do you think some bureaucrat in DC knows what's better for your child than you? Fed $$ comes w/ Fed mandates that limit local decisions.

name: Secretary Michael Watson
tweet: Thank you @cindyhydesmith for pointing out the train wreck that is Common Core and highlighting the need to get the federal government's hands out of MS's public education decision making process!

name: Secretary Michael Watson
